            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1635260078087-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1635260078087-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the<strong> browned meat-free chick'n</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency</p><p>Meanwhile, chop most of your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Fluff the<strong> basmati rice</strong> with a fork, stir through the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and season to taste – this is your<strong> coriander rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1-1635260082998-x200.jpg",
